SIMPLE: justle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Justle
<hw>Jus"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Freq. of
<ets>joust</ets>, <ets>just</ets>, <pos>v. i.</pos> See <er>Joust</er>,
<pos>v. i.</pos>, and cf. <er>Jostle</er>.]</ety> <def>To run or strike
against each other; to encounter; to clash; to jostle.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The chariots shall rage in the streets; they shall
<qex>justle</qex> one against another in the broad ways.</q>
<rj><qau>Nahum ii. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Justle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Justle
<hw>Jus"tle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Justled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Justling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To push; to drive;
to force by running against; to jostle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We <qex>justled</qex> one another out, and disputed the post for a
great while.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Justle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Justle
<hw>Jus"tle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An encounter or shock; a
jostle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Justly</ent>⟦br⟧
